                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/8300: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-08T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 8, 1935—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. Your 99, October 7, 7 p.m. You are authorized to show President Sacasa the
                    memoranda referred to and to tell him that the observations of Messrs. Wilson
                    and Beaulac contained therein accurately reflect the attitude of the
                    Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
